### Container Queries

**Container queries** style elements based on their **parent container's** size, not the viewport.

---

### Why Container Queries?

Media queries use viewport size. Container queries use **container** size. This enables truly reusable components.

```css
/* Media query - based on screen */
@media (max-width: 600px) { }

/* Container query - based on parent */
@container (max-width: 400px) { }
```

---

### Define a Container

```css
.card-wrapper {
  container-type: inline-size;
  /* or */
  container: sidebar / inline-size;
}
```

| `container-type` | Description |
|-----------------|-------------|
| `inline-size` | Query by container width |
| `size` | Query by both width and height |
| `normal` | Not a query container |

---

### Container Name

```css
.sidebar {
  container: sidebar / inline-size;
  container-name: sidebar;
  container-type: inline-size;
}

/* Query specific container */
@container sidebar (max-width: 300px) {
  .card { flex-direction: column; }
}
```

---

### Basic Example

```css
.card-container {
  container-type: inline-size;
}

@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
  }
}

@container (max-width: 399px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}
```

---

### Container Query vs Media Query

| Media Query | Container Query |
|-------------|----------------|
| Based on viewport | Based on container |
| Same for all elements | Different per container |
| Global | Local |
| Good for page layout | Good for components |
| Older, wider support | Newer, narrowing support |

---

### Container Query Length Units

Container queries introduce new units:

| Unit | Relative To |
|------|-------------|
| `cqw` | 1% of container width |
| `cqh` | 1% of container height |
| `cqi` | 1% of container inline size |
| `cqb` | 1% of container block size |
| `cqmin` | Smaller of cqi/cqb |
| `cqmax` | Larger of cqi/cqb |

```css
.card {
  font-size: 5cqi; /* 5% of container inline size */
}
```

> **Key Point:** Container queries make components truly reusable. A component can adapt whether it's in a sidebar (narrow) or main content (wide).
